git init							- Initialize a git repository in the CWD
git add .							- Add all files to stage (less .gitignore files)
git rm <file>							- Remove a file from the stage
git commit -m "...some message..."				- Commit changes
git status							- Display the current stage + changes status
git push -u origin master					- Push git commit to GitHub

** Cloning
git clone http://github.com/.../....git .../some/path/...

** Pathogen
git submodule add http://github.com/.../....git bundle/...	- Add submodule repository to vim 
cd ~/.vim/bundle/..repo..; git pull origin master		- Update the ..repo.. submodule


** Change a commit
git reset HEAD~1				- Remove previous commit but KEEP FILES.
... make changes ...			- Make changes to the files...
git push origin HEAD --force 	- Remove the pushed commit from the remote repository (e.g. GitHub)
git add .						- Re-add the files
git commit ... push ...



